<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1791,1996]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,297,1863,1888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Biology.</emphasis>
Very rare species of steppes and sunny sites, bound to its host 
<taxonomicName authority="Brulle" authorityName="Brulle" box="[1027,1372,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis box="[1027,1272,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lasioglossum pallens</emphasis>
(Brullé)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Herrmann, M., Burger, F., Muller, A. &amp; Tischendorf, S. (2003) Verbreitung, Lebensraum und Biologie der Furchenbiene Lasioglossum pallens (Brulle 1832) und ihrer Kuckucksbiene Sphecodes majalis Perez 1903 in Deutschland (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Carolinea, 61, 133 - 144." type="journal article">
Herrmann 
<emphasis box="[230,288,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[303,362,1900,1924]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the biology both of the host and the parasite. The cleptoparasite as its host occur in spring (both males and females), and are recordable only during few days or weeks from March to May. Thus it seems to be rarer than it is.
</paragraph>
